The general subject of the Praeconium Paschaze is described, and somewhat caricatured, in a letter attributed to St. Jerome, but certainly of the year 384 (Migne, Pat. Lat.9 vol. xxx. p. 182). This is addressed to a deacon of Placenza, called Praesidius, who had asked the writer to draw up for him his Praeconium.
